<p><strong data-start="184" data-end="235">Atal Residential School Admission 2026 Lalitpur</strong> is now officially open for eligible children of registered construction workers and COVID-19 affected families in Uttar Pradesh. This prestigious residential school provides <strong data-start="410" data-end="494">free quality education, accommodation, food, and holistic development facilities</strong> for boys and girls.</p>
<h2 data-start="521" data-end="581"><span style="font-size: 18pt;"><strong data-start="524" data-end="581">About Atal Residential School Admission 2026 Lalitpur</strong></span></h2>
<p data-start="583" data-end="897"><strong data-start="583" data-end="634">Atal Residential School Admission 2026 Lalitpur</strong> is being conducted by the Uttar Pradesh Building &amp; Other Construction Workers Welfare Board. Children of registered workers and beneficiaries of Mukhyamantri Bal Seva Yojana can apply for admission in <strong data-start="836" data-end="859">Class 6 and Class 9</strong> for the academic session <strong data-start="885" data-end="896">2026-27</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="899" data-end="1012">The school operates under a <strong data-start="927" data-end="970">CBSE-based residential education system</strong> with separate hostels for boys and girls.</p>
